commit.message:
Add {assert,refute}_set_equal

- Minispec expression forms are must_equal_set and must_not_equal_set.

Create minitest-bonus-assertions for release.

- This is mostly a modernized version of minitest-extra-assertions, which
  includes moving an assertion override that should not be used with modern
  Minitest.

- Gemfile.lock should not be checked in for libraries.
- Document all the things.
- Remove the override to assert_match; all someone has to do to test
  things this way is to reverse their parameters.
- Add assert_has_keys/refute_missing_keys to identify when a hash (or
  something else that responds to #has_key?) does not have the expected keys.
- Add assert_missing_keys/refute_has_keys to identify when a hash (or
  something else that responds to #has_key?) has keys that are not
  expected.
- Add assert_raises_with_message for a simple case of expecting a
  particular exception class with a specific message.
- Infected Minitest::Expectations for all the assertions.
- Implemented a special case of must_be_between because normal assertion
  infection is insufficiently flexible.
- Adapt to Hoe release process. Add Travis. Yada.

Improving comment for assert_match

Minitest has partly merged in this change, so I'm modifying
the comment to reflect how this implementation differs from theirs
(because we can safely assume at this point that this will
never be merged in).
